HOUSE JOINT RESOLUTION 1070
By McCalmon
A RESOLUTION to recognize and commend Williamson Health.
WHEREAS, it is fitting that the members of this General Assembly should specially
recognize those healthcare organizations that have achieved excellence in vital measures of
quality care and patient experience; and
WHEREAS, headquartered in Williamson County, Williamson Health is one such
distinguished healthcare system, whose flagship facility, Williamson Medical Center, has
recently earned prestigious national recognition; and
WHEREAS, Williamson Medical Center was named to Forbes Magazine's inaugural Top
Hospitals List, earning the highest overall five-star rating and standing as one of only two
hospitals in the State of Tennessee, the only hospital in Middle Tennessee, and one of just 253
hospitals nationwide to receive this distinction; and
WHEREAS, Forbes ranked hospitals based on patient outcomes, best practices, value,
and patient experience; this recognition reflects Williamson Health's steadfast commitment to
delivering high-quality, affordable health care with exceptional patient experiences; and
WHEREAS, Williamson Medical Center also received multiple 2026 recognitions from
the national Women's Choice Award program, placing the facility among the top hospitals in the
nation for excellence in patient experience, safety, and specialized clinical services; and
WHEREAS, the nine Women's Choice Awards Williamson Medical Center received in
2026 recognize excellence in comprehensive breast care, heart care, knee and hip
replacement, minimally invasive surgery, obstetrics, outpatient experience, patient experience,
patient safety, and women's services; and
WHEREAS, these honors reflect the dedication and professionalism of the
administrators, physicians, nurses, ancillary medical professionals, and staff of Williamson
HJR1070
014631
- 1 -

Health, whose tireless efforts ensure that their community has access to exceptional healthcare
services close to home; and
WHEREAS, further demonstrating its commitment to continually elevating patient care,
Williamson Health is expanding advanced cardiac imaging capabilities at Williamson Medical
Center, including the implementation of new cardiac CT technology that provides early detection
of heart disease, improved risk stratification, enhanced procedural planning, and improved
outpatient outcomes; and
WHEREAS, Williamson Medical Center will also introduce cardiac MRI capabilities,
providing non-invasive assessment of heart structure, function, and blood flow and assisting in
the diagnosis of complex heart conditions; and
WHEREAS, together, these advanced cardiac imaging technologies reinforce
Williamson Health's commitment to delivering comprehensive, state-of-the-art heart care and
ensuring earlier and more accurate diagnoses; and
WHEREAS, Williamson Health serves its community with the greatest skill and
compassion, and its dedicated professionals should be commended for their outstanding
accomplishments and continued enhancement of patient care; now, therefore,
BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES OF THE ONE HUNDRED
FOURTEENTH GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF TENNESSEE, THE SENATE
CONCURRING, that we commend and congratulate Williamson Health and its flagship facility,
Williamson Medical Center, for attaining national recognition for overall excellence in quality and
patient experience and extend our best wishes for much continued success in their future
endeavors.
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED, that an appropriate copy of this resolution be prepared
for presentation with this final clause omitted from such copy and upon proper request made to
